    "The majority of previous studies have used International Classification of Diseases (ICD) codes (Choi et al., 2016a; Li et al., 2020; Rasmy et al., 2021).",
    "The decision to use SNOMED was motivated by several factors related to our PHM use case:",
    "Detail and granularity: SNOMED CT offers a more detailed, granular system, which allows for greater specificity and detail in medical records.",
    "It's particularly useful for recording clinical details about diseases, findings, procedures, etc., that might not be adequately captured by ICD.",
